  <!-- Deep dive: Spaced repetition -->
  <section class="longform-section longform-section--alt">
    <div class="longform-container longform-container--narrow">
      <h2 class="longform-heading">Spaced repetition that works, without the PhD</h2>
      <p class="longform-body">Spaced repetition is the single most effective technique for long-term memorization. It's not debated. It's not a trend. It's how memory works.</p>
      <p class="longform-body">LanguageDen uses the FSRS algorithm, the same science behind Anki, but newer and more accurate. It tracks how well you know each word and schedules reviews at exactly the right moment: just before you'd forget.</p>
      <p class="longform-body">The difference? You don't need to configure anything. No deck settings to tweak. No intervals to calculate. No add-ons to install. You just review your cards, and the algorithm handles the rest.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

